pull.title: [MOVEONLY] Move compressor utility functions out of class
pull.body:
This is a refactor from #10785 with no functionality change.

Move the compresion utility functions out of CScriptCompressor, as a preparation for making the class templated. I'm submitting it as a separate PR as I think it's a general improvement to code readability, and to reduce the diff further on.

events.message: Move compressor utility functions out of class

events.body:
Agree with the change overall. Namespacing is good, but classes shouldn't be used for that. For readability, functions that do nothing with the instance or class state are better as utility functions.
